Whereas the Government Accountability Office found in the
			 2012 report that the estimated 20-year savings for the 2005 BRAC round
			 decreased by 72 percent from $35,600,000,000 to $9,900,000,000;

Whereas the Department of Defense would spend
			 $2,400,000,000 in a time of fiscal austerity to execute the proposed BRAC round
			 in 2015;

